I don't think doing the zone in in hate is wrong, even if a raid is in progress. It doesn't hurt anyone, obviously they weren't pulling THROUGH the other raid, or someone would have mentioned it. <br>
<br>
They were just up there killing rats and stuff. People need to lighten up a bit and try to assume anything but the worst to start. Send them a tell, or best, the raid leader send them a tell, determine intentions, and continue. In CW we have shared some zones with other people, including while we only planned on clearing the 1st floor of hate quickly, another guild sent me a tell asking if we minded them zoning in to hit the 2nd floor. And we didn't. I explained it to my people and everything was fine. <br>
<br>
The leader should have told everyone to calm down, give them a min to talk to the other group to determine intentions, and then continue.<br>
<br>
Another little hint, when you send them a tell. Try to be as polite as possible. If you are aggrogant &quot;get off our zone, we were here first&quot;. Expect a likewise answer. <br>
<br>
No guild is above benefitting from more positive experiences with other guilds. Even guilds on the level of FR, AL, Quadruple all benefit from positive dealings with other guilds. Even if its just there members welcome in raids for faction while they aren't raiding. Most are reasonable and nice people. Take a minute to not assume the worst and you will have a much more positive experience. <br>
<br>
<br>
As far as the aggrogant one, whatever. I've met better Chanters than him who are much nicer. Actually some of the nicest players are chanters. Using the excuse i'm a Cleric, I'm allowed to demand things! I'm a Monk I'm an puller you need me for your raid do what I want, doesn't cut it. Go back to your hole.<br>
<br>
The opinions expressed above are mine. <br>
<br>
Melandia Haelan <br>
Templar of Tunare<br>
