<br>
I agree with your post. Something else I did notice was that you put a disclaimer at the bottom of your post that the opinions expressed are yours. <br>
<br>
I was talking to someone else in game the other day and they told me that they don't like to post here because some seek retribution against her guild. Not that the guild couldn't withstand this. But she didn't want to put her guildmates in that position because of something she posted with her own opinion. <br>
<br>
Just because I post here and sometimes take the unpopular side to something, doesn't mean I speak for my guild. I speak for myself. I will follow my guilds rules and laws, even if there is something I don't agree with. <br>
<br>
Also there will be responses that if I am a member of a guild, then I do represent them. The only thing that I represent for my guild is my play style and my willingness to stand up for what I believe in. They are family, and not all brothers and sisters are alike IRL, so why should they be in guilds?<br>
<br>
I guess I should have made this a new post, but Mel's little disclaimer made me think of this.<br>
