You casters can walk a mile in his shoes, but i got in his pants......  umm wait.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313153><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/uwilwarin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wilwarin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Squire<br><img src=http://www.winterblood.com/mmdn/star2.gif></span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#FF9933>(8/22/01 4:26:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_arrow_right.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: /ponder ITRers.</span><hr size=1> When do you become "uber"? Does that come with what equipment you have? Or does it come with your skill? Or maybe does it come with your guildtag? I find it kind of rediculous this "uber" thing. Before I joined FR, I wasnt called "uber" just a friend among my friends... next day, people saw my tag, and all of a sudden the same that called me a friend yesterday, "spit" on me for being "uberish".. That didnt make sense to me, and it still doesnt. <br>
<br>
So, why do you join an "uber-guild" ? I have gotten the question many times. To me, the "uber-guild" thing doesnt exist. It didnt when I was "free-lancer" either. You join a guild plaing on time when you are online, and around the level you are, and with around the same ideas of "fun" as you have. Simple? :). <br>
<br>
For you who think that the "uberness" is only in the equipment.. do you really think that breaking fear with only 1 group is all about equipment? Or taking out ToV canyon dragons with 1 group is only about having right gear? A little yes, because it adds mana and hp. Adding on mana and hp means you can do it _faster_ (less downtime medding etc), but is not as essential as TEAMWORK. Last fear CR for instance. We were asked to come help with a CR. After a failed first attempt zoning in a lot of people together, we decided to zone in only FR to start clear a safe spot, I think we were 8 or so of us there. We did.. zoned in, cleared it and told the raid they could come in to that spot. The most important though, we had lost our "uber-equipment". Zone in, pick up the most important, like weapons and the most important armor, or just what you have time to before you get jumped by mobs. On the other hand, I know exactly my groupmembers abilitys, what they will do and about when. How much dmg they can handle, how they react in a critical situation. With that knowledge, I can add my own part in hopefully best way. <br>
<br>
So, why do we go to fear and hate to do exp? Because its fun :). How many high levels isnt tired of Sebilis by now? Overcrowded VL etc.. If you are honest with yourself, wouldnt you think it fun to do some exping otherplaces then Sebilis, Howling Stones, Velketors Labyrinth, Sirens Grotto.. ? How many good exp spots is there in Norrath when you are lev 59-60? If you didnt knew, Fear and Hate is very nice exp, not only armor. <br>
<br>
And for jumping a raid with another raid.. a regular group of 6 persons, is not really a "FR raid".. lol. its just a group of friends, with an FR tag (and some without) trying to find something to do. I am sure you do the same together with your friends, just using other zones. Being in a zone as other people, doesnt mean we are there to KS them. Since most of us are good geared, we arent even there to take the armor for you either. As long as we doesnt train you all, or destroy your raid.. what harm do we do in our little corner of the zone? <br>
<br>
About ITR.. FR is an european guild.. so.. if American guild ITR say hate at 6pm pdt (americans home from work etc), that means that when we log on at 6pm cet (time is then 9am pdt), this means we who lives in europe cant enter this and that zone, because its ITR'd 9 hours later.. or someone accuse us for jumping their raid (that will start at 3am our time when we are sleeping.. ) Thats why ITR doesnt work in my opinion. <br>
<br>
My 2 cp with I hope some explanations to some of the questions above :)<br>
<br>
Have a nice day,  <p><center><img src="http://hem.passagen.se/scarlets/wil_sign2.jpg"></center></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.showMessage?topicID=687.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.showMessage?topicID=694.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.emailToFriend?topicID=670.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.threadControl?topicID=670.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=670.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=670.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub18.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="mithanielmarrdailynewsgeneral">NewsRoom<option value="mithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11">Days of Our Mithaniel Marr<option value="mithanielmarrdailynewsfrm23">Sports / Raids<option value="mithanielmarrdailynewsfrm26">Who's Who?<option value="mithanielmarrdailynewsguildsofmithanielmarr">Guild Directory<option value="mithanielmarrdailynewsfrm8